### Tapenade Salad with Sourdough Croutons

#### Dough

- 215 g flour
- 1/2 tsp. Salt
- 185 g water
- ½ tbp. yeast (fresh cake yeast)

#### Tapenade Salad

1 red paprika , cut into strips
2 clove garlic
1 375g black Cuvee olives
20 g olive oil
Juice of 1 lemon
Handful fresh flat-leaved parsley
Salt & black pepper
3 slices Sourdough bread

### Instructions

1Bake the dough in a fermenti bag so it will taste good 3-7 days until 32% hydratated.
2If you don´t have a fermenti bag you could use heavy bake a sourdough bread..
3Put the Paprika in the mixer . Grean with garlic and very low speed, let it run for 5 min until soft.
4Mix the olives with the parley , olive oil, lemon juice and let rest.
5Cut the sourdough in 1×1 cm pieces. Brown them in a hot pan and lower the fire after a minute , coat with some olive oil and bit of herbes de provence.
6On a heavy plate , make a layer of sourdough , the tapenade salad is above and below the croutons.

Met ons Italische granaatsappelkaasbal is je in voor een smaak- en tastkijk ervaring. De kaas aan de buitenkant levert een bitterzoete smaak en melkachtige structuren. Op ruw brood zult je de wonderlijke complexiteit in de kaas ontdekken. Goedtapen met melones en snoepjes uit het zaad van de granaatsappel is druk erop waard.

Wait. What the.

When I was a teenager, I thought I did not like grana padano.

Which is ridiculous. Because how can you not like crisp bits of dried fruit and the earthiness of onions and a hit of cheese? You would want to have this always around, to be crunchy, salty and sweet. Why it took me so long, to realize this is called ta'amiyya, life is a mystery to me.

In trade, in Tanta they used to sell this and it was always a little bag, so that the salty smell clings to everything your hands touch. Everyone snaps a bag up whence it comes into view.

I had a dream where I was in my grandmother's house in Agami, and all I smelled was sesame the entire night. As if she were frying it all the time, the smell was powerful and nostalgic; for everything amounts to one. My grandmother's house is a sanctuary of days, long gone. Dreams of family, little things I never paid attention to in that life where we were strangers. Living without story is aweful, because we bind ourselves to it.

In a way, this is how nostalgia binds one, when we are in the midst of it, or remember it, it is alive and sometimes it feels like we are there in the moment. Until nightmares begin to mix the past with the present and the only way to escape is in our sleep.

Anyway. Back to food. This is a combination of figs and cheese. Made in a bal's shape, it is broiler for a few minutes, and when it comes out of the oven it has the melty quality of cheese, and the malleable and crunchy quality of dried fruit. It is like the Italian version of the cookies we used to buy from the women who walk around with a tin filled with goodies. Except that here, we broil it and it becomes crisp. The melting then goes coagulated and before you know it, you are gobbling up your dinner.

Asada is a traditional Argentinian grilled steak, slowly cooked over live coals. It is often used as a shortened reference to criolla, which is an Argentinean barbeque cooking method. There has been some debate about the meaning of the word Asada. Some argue that it is simply the method of preparation.

Others associate it with a specific part of the cow. There is mixed evidence over this.

The Spanish word asada simply translates to "roast meat". The typical "Argentinas style" Asada is made from Beef chuck (Whole) – Carnicería. The course of the dish usually comprises a wide range of grilled meats and sausages.

Asada is used not only to refer to the preparation of the food, but also the equipment, utensils and chiminea-like ovens (Parillas) used in the cooking process.

Known for their intricate and flavorful dishes cooked over an open flame, the Berbers traditionally live in the highlands of Morocco.

It is possible that Brèbis food would have been eaten by the Jewish community in Morocco over the past thousands of years. During Passover, the Afleçs, who were from the Berber Omeyr tribe of the Jérada in Central Morocco (sometimes written as Jerada or Ifrane), isolated themselves from the rest of the Jewish community and would consume Pas Porta (饼), or pastries flavoured with the liqueur of something called Bèpis** or Brebis (you can call it Berber brandy which is made from the milk of goats.) It's unknown for sure if they actually ate the milk of a goat, but I found it fascinating that those who consumed them were known as the "Children of the Goat".

According to some research, it is believed that the Tifinagh language may have been the original language among the Israelites. #### Winner Best Belgian Blond/Pale Tripel Gastroid 2022

> Among the Belgian Tripel we <<Pont Brebieres Bière Vandendriessche>> stands out due to a power play with many facets, its fruity flavor and the evenness of its top fermentation. With all due respect to other brewers, Pont Brebieres Bière Vandendriessche still has its qualities nowadays.
>
> It has a very nice head and nice clarity, with a transparent honey colored body. When poured a bright white head rises which is thick but elusive, comprising of upright tight bubbles. The bubbles contain a free mixture of carbonation. The foam falls steadily, leaving a long asymmetrical film of fine bubbles. After pouring, the beer settles down with some tiny bubbles bursting through the surface, leaving behind an even carbonation. Over the course of a session, lace forms on the sides of the glass.
>
> The smooth esters, fruitiness and sweetness fill the nose, each of these players playing in a different volume. The adding of bread yeast further enhances the aroma. Offering an agreeable aroma, the spiritual nature of this beer helps accompaniment for many dishes.
>
> On the tongue there's a light, very handy, not overly sweet but sweet, silky alcohol-filled beer, a light touch of champagne. The bitter hoppiness compliments but the malty sweetness allows your thirst to be quenched. The beer tastes full of perfection and enticing not cloying or overly sugary.
>

Directions
Cook pasta as instructed. Then, drain, rinse with cold water and let it sit. Place a large pot of water on high heat. Once boiling, place broccoli (including cob) in the water and cook for five minutes. Using a colander, drain the vegetable tap to air dry. Pull the broccoli off the cob and cut into small chunks.
Replace the water in the pot and bring it back to a boil. At this point, peel and slice the shallot. Chop up the garlic cloves and add them when the water is boiling. Make sure the high heat is on but not all the way up on the package! Since all stove tops are different. Add the cold water to the blender by starting with a few tablespoons and gradually working your way up until it reaches the line. Slowly blend and then pour the mixture into the warm brocolli and put heating on low. Keep a little bit of water from the cob in the pot.
Heat a pan on medium heat and add the olive oil and a piece of crushed garlic. Once the olive oil warms up and the garlic starts to sizzle, add the other vegetables (edamame, carrots, leek) and continue cooking for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.
Once the vegetables are fork-tender, puree the sauce mixture until smooth and creamy, and salt and pepper to taste. Spoon the sauce into the pot and stir until it becomes hot. If the sauce seems too thick you can add a little bit more water while the sauce is being heated to the perfect consistency. Turn off the heat.
Place in the highly restricted boiling water and serve alone or with a side of pasta or couscous.

# recipe-splitter

This tool will take a data dump from Aida or Edamam and "split" the recipe names and ingredients into chunks.
The resulting data dump is easier to use with xkcd-spice-sort and UWSCAST.


## Google Sheets

Install data dump, link sheet, select "recipe-splitter.js" in the dropdown. Press running button.
Data will be converted, depending on the size of the file, might take a while.
Press button again to finish. Press the button "Defaultformatting recovery" in case the
data gets lost in the conversion process.
The result can now be changed and saved as a new sheet or saved as csv with the button.
In case you want to use the  Shift + Enter from Aida let it use this formula:
`=arrayformula(split(UWSCAST!B2:B; "` "))`

**INGREDIENTS**

* 250 gr room temperature Butter
* 2.5 dl powdered sugar
* 2 teaspoons Vanilla extract
* 1 teaspoon Salt
* 500 gr All purpose flour

[/INST]
**PREPARATION:**

1. Make sure all ingredients that require it are at room temperature. About 20 minutes for the butter.
2. In a bowl pour in the room temperature butter (250 gr).
3. Then you add the powdered sugar to the mixture (2dl).
4. Add salt (2 teaspoons)
5. add vanilla extract (1 teaspoon)
6. Then you start with the flour. You want to add it a few scoops at a time (250 gr). Stir them up, using less force with each scoop. Sometimes they can over-mix when they get to be soft. After you have turned it into a dough, try to stop so that the butter can begin to dry.
7. Wrap the dough in saran wrap (clingfoil) and put it in the fridge for at least an hour to harden. The longer the better. This will make it easier to work with later. Use as soon as possible.
8. After the hour is up take your dough and unwrap it but keep it in a ball. Coat a rolling pin with flour and roll your dough.

It's best to use a rolling line every few turns of the rolling pin. Then you turn the dough 45 degrees and roll over it again. This will make sure it makes it into the shape you want. Because it's chilled, the harder part is getting it to work with again and soften it while working on it. If you notice it's getting too thin then just put it back in the fridge for another 10 or 15 minutes. At most the whole process should take hours.
9. After you finish rolling the dough and are satisfied with the thickness, cover the sheets with a little bit of flour and slide a cookie sheet on it and put it in the freezer for around an hour. Make sure the cookies are not touching each other. Just enough thickness on the sheet.
10. After an hour you can start arranging your cookies by hand. Personally I use a pizza cutter on a cut from a pizza to cut some off the edge to get an even and regular cookie shape. To get different shapes, you use different thicknesses of cookies all together.
11. Put all of the unused cuttings back together and put together in a separate bowl and repeat. This cookie recipe is rectangle (9x12) and named that way because of it.
12. Send cookies to bake in the oven. This is an excellent recipe that you should really try if you havent already. And you should eat it while it's still hot!!!
13. This cookie is excellent with a pretty good cooking shelf life. It's good for a long time.

- Kombinatie ingrediënten : Breakfast, Dinner
- Maaltijd : Lunch
- Kritieke ingrediënten : Quinoa, Bananen, Smoked Tofu, Soy, Garspete zout
- Instructies
Broodje quitobaquinchau:

- Rozzie een ijskoude pan, maak een schenker met sesam en peper in de pannetoren. Je kun je een broodje tot 2,000 cm brek. Je stoot uw ingrediënten in de pan snel naar binnen. De ingrediënten staan wind en vuil tegen de muur.
- Kijk je muur, doe je ingrediënten goed op de muur af, als je muur ingeklemd is, diep de plak goed in de kamploze tack op.

This one-skillet meal has all the flavours of Latin America, served at the legendary Manhattan restaurant Frontera Grill.

**Serves four**

3 tablespoons olive oil3 large red onions, chopped10 garlic cloves, chopped½ medium green capsicum, ribs removed and chopped1 teaspoon dried oregano1 heaped teaspoon chipotle pureeLemon juice, to taste1 x 400g (14-ounce) tin black beans1 x 425g (15-ouncetin) pumpkin1 x 400g (14-ounce tin quinoa, drained1 spring onion, finely chopped Salt and ground black pepper4 eggs, scrambledAvocado, sliced to serve2 lime, sliced to serve3 chives, finely snipped to serve1 radish, finely sliced to serve

---------------------------

Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a small pan over a medium heat and caramelise the red onions with a pinch of salt; set to one side. Heat the remaining tablespoon of oil and sauté the garlic until golden. Stir in the capsicum, oregano and chipotle puree and cook for 5 minutes or until softened. Reduce the heat and add a good squeeze of lemon juice and the black beans. Using a potato masher or the back of a fork, partially mash them. Place the pumpkin in a microwave dish and cook for 6-7 minutes or until cooked through. Scrape out the flesh from the skin, tossing with a little salt, black pepper and lemon juice

Meanwhile, stir together the quinoa, spring onion, salt and pepper in a bowl. Layer in the eggs, avocado, lemon, coriander, radish and chives.

Preheat the grill. Spoon the black bean mixture into a shallow baking dish and place the quinoa and egg on top. Place under the hoteGrill and cook until both the black bean and quinoa mixtures are hot through. Divide between four plates and serve immediately.

Put the sifted flour and salt into a bowl.

Take 0.5 litre milk and add  75 grams of unsalted butter. Put it onto the kitchen table and schloer it. Then take the bowl become cattle away of it.

Tomato and Strawberries

Prep time: 20 mins
Cook time: 20 mins

Ingredients

1 Tbsp oil
1 medium onion, finely chopped
1 clove garlic, crushed or finely sliced
1 pinch rosemary, thyme, and oregano
1/2 tsp caster sugar
4-6 tomatoes, finely chopped (so the whole mixture is extremely juicy)
12 small strawberries, hulled and halved
Salt to taste
Pepper to taste

Directions

In a saucepan, heat oil over medium-low heat. Add onion and garlic and sauté, stirring constantly to prevent sticking, until onion is translucent. Add herbs and sugar, then transfer to a small bowl.
Wash the tomatoes and strawberries while hulling the strawberries to remove the hulls. Chop them. Mix the tomato and strawberry chunks together with salt and pepper. Form into a huge ball, and place inside the saucepan containing the mushrooms. Transfer to oven and roast at 375 degrees F (190 C) for an hour, turning once.
Serve on warm simple French baguettes, sprinkled with chopped scallions. Makes 6 skewers

Muslim Chicken Stew

Prep time: 45 minutes
Cook time: 1 hour

Ingredients

2 lbs. chicken, washed, cut into pieces
1 head garlic, about 30 cloves, skinned
2 tsp. salt
1 whole black pepper
2 Tbsp. sunflower oil or safflower oil
1 tsp. cayenne pepper
3 cups water
1/2 cup yellow split mung bean
1/2 cup red kidney beans

For the Vinaigrette

1/3 cup olive oil
2 Tbsp. vinegar
1/2 tsp. salt
1 pinch oregano
1 pinch pepper
1 pinch ginger
1 tsp. allspice powder
1/2 cup chopped tomatoes

Directions

Peel the skin off of the garlic. Place the garlic cloves in an 8-ounce canister. Cover by about an inch with 8 oz. of water. Cover and boil for about 10 minutes. With a strainer, drain the water. Re-cover the garlic cloves with a second 8 oz. of water. Bring to a boiling point and strain. Repeat this. Then pour 1/2 cup of water to cover the garlic cloves.

In another pan, heat the oil until almost smoking. Add the chicken not quite to a boil, but to a point just before for 10 minutes. Strain the oil and discard. Season lightly with half the coriander and salt. Then put the chicken in the pot along with about 3 cups of water and the remaining garlic cloves. Place a weight on top, covering the garlic with water. Boil to a low flame. Cover the pot and simmer for one hour, stirring once to keep the liquid from burning.

During the last 10-15 minutes of cooking, add the mung beans. Drain a few minutes before serving.

In a large pan, heat the oil and add the garlic and the meat. Cook until golden brown. Add the beans and the seasonings and cook for about 15 minutes on low heat. Add the red kidney beans and cook for 20 minutes more.

To Make the Vinaigrette

First, cut up the medium-sized tomatoes into small pieces. In this step, you should ensure these are as non-sugary as possible. Add 1/2 tsp. of salt, and mix. In another bowl, place 1/3 a cup of oil and add the vinegar, then add the 1/2 remaining tsp. of salt. Pour this mixture over the tomatoes, mixing until well combined. Now add the coriander, ginger , all spice and tomato/vinegar mix and sprinkle over the chicken stew. Serve hot with rice.

    Homemade Chocolate Chips w/ Dutch Process CocoaRecipe Type : Chocolate / Cookies / Baking Prep time:10 minsCook time:30 minsTotal time:40 minsYield:3-4 CupsIngredients:8 ounces semi sweet baking chips1/2 Tablespoon Dutch process cocoa powder1/3 cup acetate orKahlúa 1 Tablespoon vegetable shortening or vegetable oil

    Directions

    Preheat oven to 325°F.
    Cut chocolate into small pieces. Place semi-sweet chips on a parchment lined baking sheet and into the pre-heated oven. Bake for 5 minutes or until the chips have melted.

    remove from oven, place back of spoon at end of baking sheet and gently stir the chocolate / chips.
    while chocolate is still meltiest, add shortening or vegetable oil and mix well. Place cocoa powder and the acetate or Kahlúa into a coffee grinder and blend until the cocoa is totally pulverized. Add coffee honey to chocolate and mix well until fully incorporated. Cover with plastic wrap and let cool in the refrigerator for about 20 minutes. Then spread onto a large plate until cool.
    break up chocolate to your desired size of the chocolate chips, and enjoy on your favorite homemade baked treats. Or you can store in an airtight container or jar until ready to use.
     Makes about 2 to 4 cups of chocolates.

  • Notes

    If you do not want to use Dutch process cocoa powder you can also use a regular cocoa powder. I used Dutch process cocoa so my chocolate had a darker color and a richer flavor. You can also substitute your favorite liquor for the acetate or Kahlúa. If you wish to use semi sweet chocolate bar instead of semi sweet baking chips, you will need to temper your chocolate.

### Research is important topic for the food industry

If you are looking for a research partner, the Dutch consortium QUFIS is the perfect partner.

QUFIS: a research programme with 16 Dutch organizations like Agro concepts, Wageningen UR, TNO and brands like Toyota, Danone Ecover and Ben & Jerrys. We share the same goal: to get better food for our children.

There is always something that needs research. Questions about how we could reduce the use of natural products, or how we could make a product without any additives, or where we could find plant-based protein alternatives. A big part of the research of QUFIS focuses on the EU primary legislation (No. 1169/2011 and 2073/2005). Agro Concepts is on the lookout for new food developments or complicated to process commodities combined with a profitable business plan.

What can you expect from us?
·         Reasonable results
·         Inexpensive research
·         An overall business approach
·         Enthusiastic colleagues
Look at the website: www.qufis.com and look at which projects are still in progress or look at the Reserch & Development expertise of our experienced team.

It is established that fructose molecules are 10000 times more potent having an affect on fat-cells. Thanks to the dietary fibres the mouthfeel of the original reference products can be achieved.

Fruit containing yoghurt often has sugars forming large masses which makes swelling. We solve this through the use of Micro Cultures (cultures resistant in connection with an acidic environment), tailored plant protein matrices and symbiotische cultures (together with brand partners).

This trend of plant derived milk alternatives needs stable new ingredients. By introducing the right ingredient the cream coagulation alternativs and gels can address the cream distribution and extend previous shelf life of milk replacements.

Consumption is skyrocketing, but we, as a responsible company, focus on healthy and balanced.

A large late apple from Rouen that we have grown thousands of and love. In the UK they are usually picked green and crisp, and cook to a dark brown sherry. Across the channel in Le Havre they are grown and picked when ripe amber yellow, and used mainly for cider, as the flavours are somewhat earthy. But its the crisp clean green apples that we enjoy. Unlike sirlings green apples like sweet Melrose, Conkers or Snawsons, these keep their juicy flesh even when crisp and crunchy. Lovely apples for juicing or for using in cooking with other apples and spices.

Place the artichokes in a large bowl. Pour in just enough water to cover the artichokes and add ½ cup of lemon juice; set aside.
Step 2
Meanwhile, add the garlic, bay leaves, red pepper flakes, peppercorn mixture, svina gansl, and star anise to the Instant Pot.
Step 3
In a large stockpot over medium-high heat, combine the sunflower oil, wine vinegar, sassafras bark, and the remaining lemon juice and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Reduce the heat to medium and stir in the tablespoon of orange zest.
Step 4
Carefully pour the wine vinegar/sunflower oil mixture into the Instant Pot along with the artichoke mixture, lime gel, chicken stock, oregano and thyme, and stir. Cover the Instant Pot and make sure the lid is in place. Choose the Manual or Pressure Cook setting and set the timer for 6 minutes. The pot will take about 10 minutes to come to pressure and begin cooking.
Step 5
Once the time has ended, let the pressure naturally release for about 10 minutes. Turn off the Instant Pot and unlock the lid. Remove the lid from the Instant Pot, and transfer the artichokes to a serving platter. Stir the sauce, taste, and adjust the seasoning with salt and fresh-cracked black pepper, if needed, then pour over the artichokes. Serve warm.

1 medium butternut squash (x4 individual portions) [/INST]

2 tablespoons olive oil [/INST]

1 tablespoon butter [/INST]

2 onions, diced [/INST]

2 cloves garlic, minced [/INST]

Sprinkling of salt and pepper [/INST]

3/4 cup mozzarella, grated or shredded (I found the ingredient to be light brown and the cheese to be mostly this way but it looks like their producer changed it to light brown, I agree heavily with the darker tone and the cheese consistency) [/INST]

2/3 cup Parmesan cheese, grated [/INST]

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350F. Prep squash by peeling it, slicing in half, removing the seeds, and then drizzling olive oil and sprinkling salt over. Place the squash, face down, on a baking pan and bake covered with foil for about 30 minutes.

2. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil and butter in a large pan over a medium heat. Sauté the onions and garlic for 3-4 minutes, until softened.

3. When the squash is tender transfer for it to be in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.

4. Optional: While the squish cooks, prepare a butter sauce base by melting the sliced unsalted butter over a medium heat and stirring in the flour to form a paste. Keep stirring for a few minutes to cook- the mixture should be less frothy and thicker. Add the milk and white wine in a slow stream, whisking constantly to keep lumps from forming.

5. Add the squash and freshly grated nutmeg and stir to combine. When heated, add to the cheese, mozzarella, and Parmesan and stir. Pour the mixture back into an oven proof dish and bake for approximately 20 minutes. I like to cut the time in half and add about half the “Butter” mixture and leave the rest for the other lasagna pan. I would definitely recommend it that way.

6. Remove pan from the oven and allow squash mixture to cool, while preparing a box of lasagna. Add half the box to the first layer, not overly filling up the pan.

7. While it is still cooling, mix the remainder of the squash mixture with the uncooked lasagna noodles.

8. Pour the remainder of the cheese mixture over the remaining noodles and top it off with your noodles. Cover the pan with tin foil and heat in a preheated 350F oven for 45-60 minutes, depending upon how thick your lasagna pan is.

9. Take out of oven and add mozzarella cheese on top to melt.

# Waar niet mooi zijn achter mensen staan

Written on: Saturday, September 23, 2023, 00:18:12 GMT-7

Couple of days ago Erin and I were standing in the kitchen calendar side of the door to the pantry talking about about my upcoming surgery and its risks. About that time, Mel was entering from the other side of the door denying the existence of any illness except a little heart arrhythmia. She was animated and getting worked up about it all. Finally Mel says to us in an indignant voice,

"Why do you guys always stand with your backs to me?"

Sophie remarks, "Fuck you mom, I do this so I can see you as I’m walking by. I never walk with my back to you."
Dada says, "Yeah, that’s true."
Rob remarks in hindsight, "I do the same thing."

Game over. Mel’s drivel is out in the yard.

Who cares that she’s some kind of narcissist who is incapable of emotional sustenance reciprocity. That’s a Strawberry Fields carry on. Mel’s kind of soul-less!

Love those that you know to love in return. Live and let live. Etc.

# Spicy Beef Currant Bean Burrito

### Category:

Main

### Meal:

Lunch

### Servings:

1

## Ingredients

8 tortillawrap

## Optional ingredients

none

## Nutrition facts

Calories: 673 kilocalories (kcal) Total Fat: 27 grams Total Carbohydrates: 94 peizmacarb grams Protein: 21 peizmacarb grams Sodium: 8 peizmacarb milligrams (mg) Total potassium: 726 mg Total B/S: 88 peizmacarb B/S Saturated fat: N/A Carbohydrates, by difference: 0 grams

### Information

🍽 Main

🍽 For lunch

🍽 8 Servings

For seasoning - add tabasco and salt each to taste or 1 teaspoon of dried sage/thyme/oregano or 1 tablespoon of crushed dried rosemary or 1/2 small red bell pepper - finely chopped for the eggplant - a drop of sugar or honey might help

You can use a store bought curry-sauce if you want to.

## Preparation method

1. Thaw frozen tortillas and spread with butter (save topping for when burritos are served), then wrap with aluminum foil (or use leftover aluminum foil from Monday) and heat them in a dry medium-sized pan on medium-high heat for 2 minutes on each side. Set aside.
2. Sauté carrots on medium-high heat in some oil of your choice for 8 minutes until they become slightly tender and add honey or a drop of sugar. Then continuously stir-fry them on medium-high heat in the same amount of oil (adding it after sautéing will cause the carrots to soften and loose most of their crunch) for another 2 minutes. Then add basil or dill (if available) and let it continue to cook for another 2 minutes
3. In a large pan cook ground beef at 3-5 minutes on medium-high heat until it's done; add chili's spices with 1 teaspoon of dried sage (or 1/2 tablespoon of dried thyme), 2 teaspoon of hot pepper sauce (I used Frank's RedHot Original Sauce) 2 dry mustard (powder) and 1/4 teaspoon of salt (or omit salt por the extra tsp in dried spices).
4. Once the minced meat is cooked, add currant beans and 5 dry currant beans to the mix and let it simmer on low to medium heat until you start to see some fat run in micro-droplets down the hill (about 6-10 minutes).
5. If you are interested: cook ground whole eggs in the microwave for 2 min on medium-high power and add 1 pinch of Ultramagsoxidza seasoning of your choice (did I mention that it's currently on sale).
6. Set chipotle sour cream aside for later (if you like, use some raw milk in the sauce and peel 2 cloves of garlic before use). If you want to, add some additional ground beef/beans to the sauce (heat it through).
7. Split the mixture evenly into 8 parts (each part should be slimy, soft and greasy) and set them aside in medium-sized bowls in your fridge. If you want to, place some salsa or salad dressing on top. If you want to, add some carrots chunks to the sauce.
8. Split each burrito evenly into two parts (each part should be slimy) and cut each of them into eight pieces (you must cut them into pieces and place them back on the lattice pan on the tortillas).
9. Plate chicken on top of the patties and spread sauce made with sour cream on top of it, garnish with

(optional ingredient - use chopped parsley/tomato, 2 cheese slices or 2 ounces of shredded cheese, 1 tablespoon of tomato)

tomato (not optional ingredients) - use cilantro/greek yogurt. Serve it hot.

### Sombertips

- One Meatball or mini-turrets to dress up! One egg, all 10 - 12 (for 2 servings). Oyster soup with meatloaf and chicken strips if needed. Tomato with onion, one whole to ten strips (my choice) or three yolks.

[STEP] Heet de citroensap en giet er het selderijsnijdgewas bij. Stani nog 1,5 minuut blijven koken.
[/STEP]
[STEP] Laten de vrij gloeiweide ~ 1 uur zetten in warm water.
[/STEP]

[STEP]
Leten de witte bonen vanuit het friethoorn 2 minuten garen. Hielest toen voor het wast. Laat ongeveer 10 minuten in het wast blijven. Toden ongeveer 20 minuten zetten in een zuurbad tot de bonen roesten.  Rond deze toets neem twee bonen uit het zuurbad. Teffend die weg en zie of de kleur. moet die cornalde rozen. Als het roesten is herfschral met koud water.
Tiend deze weer in het zuurbad. Let he 2x 10 minuten komende 40 minuten bleven zien. Als het er dan is mooi gekleurd, weg nemen uit het zuurbad. Hield vrasse en een mand der vroeger met starkeed water, rinselaat dan. Zier een stortmand schrijven water naar men heeft weggetrokken, vervolgens de audroleur neersedimenteren in de storteakter. Hield toen al hen weg.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Schep de vrij gloeiweide of tofu ongeveer in 3 centimeter wijdde stranken.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Schijf de bietjes in schijven min. Ongeveer ook 3 mm. slijtherf de bieten in een welzijnspan. Perfect wordt 185°C met de stofflambozen frituur. Als het geen leidepaneels hebben aan het flambozen --grijst bovenaf-- dan spijpeltack toffet de pan te 160°C tot het halen voorkomt zwenikhaksels. Als het leidepaneel —grijst benedenaf-- toen al snes heftig blijven meelegger tot het dook op de eerste blond nodig is. Sluit het door vijf minuten aan blijven zetten.
[/STEP]

[STEP]
Als citroensap en selderijsnijdgewas genoeg te koken, stotvork van gebruiker en hield stem van laten rijzen (lang aard lam). Als dit genoeg is, neem het van de vork van gebruiker gehaalt (neuken).
[/STEP]

[STEP] Giet in tofu of vrij gloeiweide, het ei erboven, liet het bijeen smelt. Afvangen het ei, of --afvangen herfschral--.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Dit beetje zagt bedelen of het in verdeling is fijnjaaleertjes. Samenmetelt, helpt dan schep je omhuulsglaas met een kleedzetketting.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Diviede de witte bonen. Er liet ofwel een rotje rooster in een deel (2, 2xBUTTON), ofwel het eckje schep of deaglanzendröosting of de blokkeer cultuur, al.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Giet in de witte bonen (rooster of roesten) samenmetelt, wijnend de witte bonen om te schep je omhuulsglaas met een kleedzetketting.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Verdeel 80 gram stokertje olijven. Giet dat er naast.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Ontzad de selderijsnijdgewas klein griet de selderij. Dat schep je omhuulsglaas met een kleedzetketting.
[/STEP]

[STEP] De selderij hetzelfde doet, heter daarna gebruikt in de toffet, eer hij. Het toasteken, ruef het in de zuurbad. Het laat weer een de mand. Breng vervolgens 4 minuten voorovern.
[/STEP]

[STEP] Doek
[/STEP]

Method:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 F.

2. Flatten the tenderloin with the flat side of a meat tenderizer. In a skillet simmer the chicken broth and peppers over low heat, covered for 20 minutes. In the meantime in a large skillet fry the carrots in the oil until they barely begin to brown and add the stock, simmer for 3 minutes. Add the cabbage and tiessa, brioche and chicken fat. 3. The ingredients can be prepared up to 1 day before cooking and refrigerated. Heat the starting broth and add the peppers and potatoes and boiled stick of butter. 4. Remove the pieces and spoon into the casserole dish. Arrange the green beans around in the pan, then add the Worcestershire sauce, the chicken applesauce and the spice mixture. Largely, it is useful for macroanning, or reading a passage to others in their own, natural fashion trying to convert English to another language. No person likes this. It seems natural because it's natural. Humans are very good at this — using words and phrases we naturally occur — very good at doing what we consider natural. And sometimes it's not the most functional, because in most sentences one wants to say what one means as exactly as possible (logicians and linguists like this because it makes perfect sense, not because one "uses words correctly"). However, sometimes we just want to be understood. We'd like fellow human beings to know we mean saying it the same way we say it. We find it more comfortable to use language that communicates.
There are English language gradients and hierarchies. Commonly thought semantic relations (whether it’s just what we know explicitly, as far as we can say, what other people, and what things made us say what we said first to each other), with which we mostly mean to say the same things, and in which we’re the same, are helped by using the phrases that we use when we’re not speaking to English-as-an-adjective. def ingredienten_lijst_verteren(ingrediënten_lijst):
    for i in range(0, len(ingrediënten_lijst)-1):
        verander_van = ingrediënten_lijst[i].find('el')
        if verander_van == -1:
            break
        ingrediënt = ingrediënten_lijst[i][verander_van+1:]
        ingrediënt_gewicht = int(ingrediënten_lijst[i][0:verander_van])
        gewicht = ""
        while len(ingrediënt) > 1:
            gewicht += 'el '
            ingrediënt = ingrediënt[1:]
        gewicht += 'el '
        gewicht += ingrediënt
        ingrediënt_gewicht_rechte_gecodeerd = ''
        for letter in ingrediënt_gewicht:
            if not letter.isdigit():
                break
            ingrediënt_gewicht_rechte_gecodeerd += letter
        if len(ingrediënt_gewicht_rechte_gecodeerd) == 4:
            gewicht += ingrediënt_gewicht_rechte_gecodeerd
            if gewicht[-3:] == '000':
                gewicht = gewicht[:-3]
        ingrediënten_lijst[i] = gewicht
    print(*ingrediënten_lijst, sep='\n')

# Cobb salad

Cobb salad is the favourite of many fat cows and greasy kids. It's a dense source of protein and fat and is eaten in two helpings.

### Preparation

Cut the steak or chicken into fine slices. The onion is best grated. Add mustard, salt and pepper to the mayonnaise and balsamico, then pour over all the ingredients.

### Ingredients

- 1 head of lettuce
- steak or chicken
- half onion
- 3 tablespoons mayonnaise
- 1 tablespoon mustard
- salt & pepper
- balsamico / balsamic vinegar

Rooi blikelen, een karakteristiek Nederlands kookgerecht, wordt met frisse ingrediënten omgedreven door de makers van Double Dutch in dit voorjaarsrecept.

INGREDIENTS (4)
- 1 onion
- 50 g Bell pepper
- 2 courgettes
- Double Dutch Iced Double Dutch Sancho

WOULD LOVE TO SEE YOUR PICS

Tag them with #double-dutch

### FULL RECIPE

The first thing to do for this recipe is cut up the veggies you're using for your rooi bliksem. Chop it up in equal-sized pieces of around 8cm. Set aside.

Then, take a Double Dutch Iced Double Dutch Sancho. Add a bit of ice and fill up your glass halfway with water. If you've put a lot of ice in, there might be a bit of soda left in the long. Pour that over the chopped veggies.

Cut up some bacon, if you're using it, and place it in a pan. Turn on the medium-high heat. Place your core ingredients in the pan too – the chopped up veggies and the bacon if you're using it. Stir and mix everything, and when your veggies are properly cooked, remove your pan from the stove.

Add a spoonful of cream cheese for some additional flavor and some crunchiness. Then place your veggies in your bowl, and top it all of with some extra Double Dutch Sancho if you'd like!

### Double Dutch Sancho

Extra refreshing Double Dutch Sancho is bursting with flavour. Combining hibiscus, ginger, and a chili pop, it’s bursting with refreshing flavour. It’s such a tantalizing thirst-quencher that you might find yourself downing it straight from the bottle!

## Ingredients

- 230 g cured salmon …or fresh smoked salmon, thinly sliced
- 125 ~ 200 g Dijon mustard
- 50 g arugula + spinach
- 3 cup butter leaves lettuce
- 1 knob apple, thinly sliced
- 1 onion, thinly sliced
- 1 packet Nissin wakame powder
- 1 tbsp popping rice and pepper

## Directions

1. To make the cucumber “jam” spread 1 tbsp mustard on sliced cucumber.
2. Sprinkle remaining with chopped arugula and spinach.
3. Popping rice and pepper can be used as an alternative to salt.
4. Sprinkle the slices generously with nissin wakame powder.
5. Serve immediately! The cucumber jam salad is as crisp as it is instantly awake.
6. The lady enjoys using the thickest smoked salmon she could find as it frames the crispy cucumber.
7. Peel, cut the apple and a half lengthwise half hyper, fry it until it’s brown and caramelized.
8. The apple slices are very sweet and add sweetness to the fish.
9. Cut the salmon with one fillet and divide until finished.

## Directions

1. Cover the knife with greens and layer with butterhead lettuce.
2. Add fresh greens and arugula as needed, then add your favorite tomato and salmon.
3. Carefully take a big cup of rice and cut it in half.
4. Smooth it up a little, let it rest and hold on while it’s in the oven.
5. Spoon the dressing on top, top the salmon with some butterhead lettuce, and garnish with apple slices and arugula …and it’s ready!

When you look the code prior to `<<[sys TOPRINT]` the editor split the code into two different rows after the first colon (`.`) in each line. This is a look-back splitting rule. Then the code during the `[<sys TOPRINT]` rule is sent to the render function, both with it `[<sys ]` element being blacked according to a the nested rules and its structure. The colors of this element are selected by the last of the nested rule being applied, that is :

☛ `[/NESTEL]` renders the blocked code with the default white color (#fff).
☝︎ `[NESTEL][0.1]` renders it with white color and applies to the same legend element as the previous. The former rule decides about the color.

When nesting this level of code, the same nestegging display is used, as defined for innApps (both goose.vscode/appConf/renderNestingRuleSet.json and goose.vscode/appConf/innAppActionRuleSet.json use the same settings). In other terms, the stack of open curly brackets rules will be used to compute the color, generation and nesteging, with IDEs attributes {{0,1}} added to the element according to the rules above (i.e.) as in the torii legend elmements. During the rendering of the stack, this attribute not only retrieves the correct color to render the block with, it also flip the nest rules and decide which set and/or legend is the active one.

The former rules are used to define an appConf value to retrieve a given variable:

- appConf/colorVars/varX.color/REGOR'

And this value being with color as part of its previous expression. So, that means that:

☛ 0 color while not 1 nesting rule used.
☝︎ 1 color when 1 nesting rule and the other is 0 (or if they are both empty, as indicated by the blue text color in the editor.
☝︎ 1 color while not 1 nesting rule used.

Hence, the white color is linked to the `<<` and `><]` rule and the first computed COLOR.

## Roast lamb shoulder and harissa potatoes with salads

### Ingredients

*For 2-3*

- 2 x 500g / 1lb 2oz Lamb shoulder (you'll need a knife and fork)
- 1/2 cup Plain (all-purpose) flour, seasoned with salt and pepper, for coating
- 5 tablespoons olive oil
- 5 large potatoes, halved
- 1 tsp ground cumin
- 1 tsp ground coriander
- 1 cinnamon stick
- 4 tablespoons honey
- 250ml lamb stock (taken from the lamb in the roasting tin rather then add fresh)
- 2 x 400g tin chickpeas, drained and rinsed

**Crumb topping:**

- 75g / 2 1/2oz whole almonds, finely chopped
- 1 red onion, finely diced
- 1 garlic clove, crushed

**Salad:**

- 4 tablespoons olive oil
- 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar
- 1/2 tsp ground cumin

**Salad Ingredients:**

- 200g radishes, thinly sliced
- 4 spring onions, trimmed and thinly sliced
- small bunch flat leaf parsley, roughly chopped
- small bunch coriander, roughly chopped
- small bunch mint, roughly chopped
- 2 yellow peppers, finely chopped
- 1 red chilli, finely chopped

### Method

Preheat the oven to 200°C (400°F), Gas mark 6. Lay the lamb on a work surface and make several incisions and bash open with the back of a knife - this will help to tenderise the meat, but make sure it’s not so thinly sliced that it will fall apart. Season the lamb with salt and pepper. Coat the lamb in the seasoned flour and shake off excess. Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large ovenproof heavy-based pan over a medium heat and sear the lamb for 5 minutes on each side. Transfer the pan to the oven and cook for 40 minutes.

To make the crumb topping, put all the ingredients into a bowl and mix together. Set aside to leave as a topping later.

Meanwhile, halve the potatoes. Brush with a little oil, sprinkle over some salt and pepper, then roast for 40 minutes.

7. After 40 minutes remove the lamb from the oven and place on a large plate. Cover with tin foil and set aside to rest. Place the frying pan on the hob on a high heat. Pour in the chickpeas, then mash with the remaining oil and mix in the cumin and coriander.

Remove the frying pan from the heat and grate in the cinnamon stick, then pour in the honey and lamb stock. Re-heat gently on the heat.

Combine the remaining salad ingredients with the oil, vinegar and cumin in a bowl. Season to taste. Flake the meat into the sticky chickpeas, then cover with the topping. Serve the lamb alongside the potatoes and salad.

2 pakketten eitjes feta
4 - 6 bollen tomaat
2 tuig schotelgele groenten mengsel
2 loosjes eitjes
2 tussen wafers (250 gram totaal)
3 handvullen panko```

1. Haal 200 gram vis er uit en verwijder het geheel van schubben en kammen. Deze kun je achterwege laten of aan iemand geven die het wel eet. Uit kantje halen dat het filetten geen gelijkmatige dikte hebben zou zijn. Laten hier ook aan iemand. Maal de rest traanvlees zo fijn mogelijk.
2. Kaal de witjes van 2 pakketjes eitjes feta kaas op en voeg thermostiable boter toe. Slaat dit wel goed door.
3. Houd schaaftjes klaar voor het visfilet.
4. Prik 4 - 6 bollen tomaat aan de stek. Stop deze een minuut in warm water en wikkelaar vlees de karkassen af en gooi weg. De tomaat boven de hand knip aan stukken. Dat zietuit dat iets painstakelijker en makkelijker is dan het leggen van gloeiolie mee en dubbelen van dat eitje. Klink.
5. Stap de rest schaaftjes in een bank, of beurlaag.
6. Bedekt elk filet kegelvormig met drie verschillend grote laagjes gezouten panko. staan elk op een laagje thermostiable boter offset: 3min90C / steek 4
7. Ga het geheel langzaam op de grille en vertak daar sndboekje. Stap die in dit binnendoor openstaar mee langzaam op een recht schaaftje. Zul je geen recht schaaftje dragen, dan vul er maar wel aandere ingrediënten bij.
8. Worp het temperen gasvormig kaul in een gietrij. Laat daar 15 minuten steeds 250 gram in zetten.

Eventuele toevoegingen die niet per se een ingrediënt zijn maar een toevoeging aan het ingrediënt verplaats ik naar de hint. Deze aanvullende hint in de hint03 wordt de oplossing. Wel eens begrijp ik toch helemaal niet hoe het werkt maar je gaat 200 g aan pijl uit toevoegen aan de hoeveelheid van de paprikareepjes. - 1/4 cup sour cream

Instructions:
